-- General Growth Properties Names Brookfield's Flatt as Chairman of Board
-- B y   P e t e r   W o o d i f i e l d
-- 2010-10-05T10:43:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-05/general-growth-appoints-brookfield-s-bruce-flatt-as-chairman-of-new-board.html
General Growth Properties Inc., the
second-largest U.S. mall owner, said  Bruce Flatt  will become
chairman of the board after the company emerges from bankruptcy
next month.  Flatt, chief executive officer of  Brookfield Asset
Management Inc. , was among nine individuals appointed to the new
board, Chicago-based General Growth said today in a statement.
General Growth Chief Executive Officer  Adam Metz  will also join
the board.  General Growth is scheduled to seek court approval in
November to exit bankruptcy after receiving financial
commitments from Brookfield, Fairholme Capital Management LLC
and Pershing Square Capital Management LP.  Other directors include Richard “Ric” Clark, chief
executive officer of Brookfield Properties Corp.,  Cyrus Madon ,
senior managing partner at Brookfield Asset Management,  Sheli Rosenberg , currently lead director of General Growth, and John
Haley, a current General Growth board member. None of the
company’s other senior executives will be on the board,
according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Peter Woodifield  in Edinburgh at 
 pwoodifield@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Blackman at   ablackman@bloomberg.net . 